# 3. 灯る火

Staff Member: Nice performance! Let's take a brief break here!
Minori: That...
Minori: Was such an amazing performance...! How awesome was ReLight?!
Shizuku: Incredible! They sang three songs, but it was over before we knew it.
Haruka: Despite going first, they ended up leaving the biggest impression on everyone.
Haruka: The other groups are all really good, but they definitely stood out the most.
Airi: Yeah... We really can't ask for a better performance partner.
Haruka: Airi?
Airi: I'm gonna go grab some water. Are any of you thirsty?
Shizuku: U-Umm... I'm okay, but...
Airi: Alright, I'll be right back!
Minori: A-Airi...?!
Airi: Phew... Some cold water was just what I needed.
Airi: We're gonna be moving around a lot after this, so I need to stay hydrated.
Airi: (Still... ReLight totally blew the roof off this place.)
Airi: (Haruka was right. A bunch of groups performed after ReLight, but they ended up leaving the biggest impression.)
Airi: (We really can't ask for a better collaboration partner, but the thought of having to dance next to them is starting to feel like a scary prospect...)
Airi: (Performing alongside ReLight is a good opportunity for us to improve our singing and dancing skills... But it doesn't look like it's going to be an easy feat.)
Airi: (What should we do...?)
Idols: ReLight leading off Idol Lovers. It's so obvious that they're getting special treatment.
Airi: Huh...?
Idols: I guess that's what happens when you have a famous producer backing you. I mean, they went from zeroes to heroes in seconds. Someone at their agency is definitely the puppet master.
Idols: When you put it that way, is there even any point in trying? Ugh, now I really wish I had joined a different agency.
Airi: What?
Airi: (How can they say that? Were they not looking at the stage just now?)
Airi: (There's no way you can put on a performance like that unless you put in the work and effort. They should know that!)
Airi: (I can't let this slide. I have to say something.)
Akari: It's okay, Momoi.
Airi: E-Enosaki...?!
Idols: Wait, what...? Enosaki's here?
Idols: We need to leave.
Airi: Oh...
Airi: I-I'm sorry. Umm...
Akari: No, I should be the one apologizing to you! I feel awful about you hearing those rumors about us.
Akari: Also, Momoi, it looked like you were about to go and say something to them... Thank you.
Airi: Huh...?
Airi: No, you don't need to thank me. I just got so irritated at what they said.
Akari: But that made me really happy! It's so nice to know that you'd defend us!
Airi: Oh...
Airi: Still, are you sure about this? They said some really awful things just now.
Airi: Regular people spreading around those kinds of rumors is one thing, but we're talking about people in the industry here. Aren't you worried that it's gonna affect your work...?
Akari: Yeah, we are... And we had a lot of trouble coming to terms with it when it first started happening.
Akari: MORE MORE JUMP! hasn't acted this way, but whenever we collaborate with other groups, they often tend to be wary of working with us.
Airi: Then...
Akari: But our producer told us to not lose sight of our goal.
Airi: Huh...?
Akari: He said, “You will encounter naysayers along the way as you strive to become top idols.”
Akari: “So, don't give them any heed. You don't even have to try to shake them off.”
Akari: “But someday...”
Akari: “You're going to show them by spreading or inspiring hope in them.”
Airi: ...!
Akari: After hearing that, we were completely on board.
Akari: He's right about us still having a lot of work to do and how we aren't able to reach many people yet. That's on top of all the comments and criticism we get...
Akari: But we only have one goal. To keep spreading as much hope as we can to as many people as we can.
Akari: As long as we focus on that, I'm sure people will start understanding what we're trying to do.
Airi: Enosaki...
ReLight Member: Akari! Do you have a minute? I wanna make sure we have that one part down.
Akari: Oh...
Akari: Just a minute! Be right there!
Akari: Sorry, Momoi, I didn't mean to make you spend your break talking about something so gloomy...
Airi: No, don't worry about that.
Airi: Actually, you gave me a really valuable piece of information. Good luck with that part by the way.
Akari: Thank you! I hope we get to chat about something more fun next time!
Airi: (I think I finally understand why ReLight's able to put on such astounding performances.)
Airi: (They're just like us... They want to spread hope to as many people as they can...)
Airi: (And they're fully committed to that.)
Airi: (Also, more importantly...)
Akari: He said, “You will encounter naysayers along the way as you strive to become top idols.”
Airi: (They're taking their job as idols seriously.)
Airi: (But we're no different from them.)
Airi: (Which means we should be more than capable of putting on better performances.)
Airi: Challenge accepted.
Airi: We'll be ready in time for Idol Lovers... We're gonna show everyone that we can perform on the same level as them.
